Three Rivers Analyses Repository

Sam Safran / Last updated: 2023-12-24

This site hosts analyses conducted for the Three Rivers Park District.

Pages found under the Analyses header include:

Setup

  • Data preparation | Walks through the process of importing data from TRPD Access Databases and geodatabases into R for subsequent analyses. Also performs basic data cleaning and processing up front that is used in all subsequent analyses.

Birds

  • Regional trends | Presents Breeding Bird Survey data and modeled abundance indices from survey routes in MN Bird Conservation Region #23 (Prairie-Hardwood Transition). In other analyses these regional trends are compared with trends in the parks.

  • Grassland birds: community-level dynamics | Analyzes how grassland bird diversity has changed over time in restored prairies at Crow-Hassan park.

  • Grassland birds: population-level trends | Analyzes how populations of grassland species have changed over time in restored prairies at Crow-Hassan park.

  • Grassland birds: park vs.regional trends | Compares species-level trends in Crow-Hassan with regional trends from BBS data.

  • Forest birds: woodland restoration surveys | Analyzes bird communities in restored woodlands, with an emphasis on comparing responses to different woodland restoration methods.

  • Bike trail surveys | Assesses species-level trends from park district bike trail surveys. Presents comparisons with regional trends from BBS.

  • 2022 Big Year of Birds: year in review | Summarizes eBird data submitted across all Three Rivers parks in 2022.

  • Christmas Bird Count scouting | A tool for identifying birds that have been recently seen in a Christmas Bird Count. Used for the West Hennepin CBC.

Other analyses

  • Species lists | A tool to generate species lists for the park district and individual parks, using data form the Global Biodiversity Information Facility.

  • Mapping prescribed burns | Code to generate yearly maps of burned units and animations showing burns over time in each park.

  • Lupine | A simple analysis of plant survey data to examine the density/cover of wild lupine in Crow-Hassan Park. Developed to support efforts to potenitally reintroduce the Karner Blue Butterfly.
